{"TopicId":141180,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[Minimum KSP version 1.11] Easy Vessel Switch (EVS) v2.3","CreatedByName":"IgorZ","CreatedById":155445,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-04T09:29:41Z","PageNum":7,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"IgorZ","CreatedById":155445,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-04-24T04:23:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Ch1 style=\u0022color:#000000;font-size:20px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://kerbal.curseforge.com/projects/easy-vessel-switch-evs/files/2702979\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E1.11 (April 23rd, 2019)\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/h1\u003E\n\u003Cul style=\u0022color:#000000;font-size:13px;padding:0px 0px 0px 30px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\n[Change] KSP 1.7 compatibility.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-04-28T02:20:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/155445-igorz/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022155445\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/155445-igorz/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@IgorZ\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there any reason why I am seeing multiple copies of the\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EKSPDev_Utils.1.2.dll\u003C/strong\u003E file in different mods?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am looking into an issue with another mod, and I found this file in the following mod directories:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\n./GameData/EasyVesselSwitch/Plugins/KSPDev_Utils.1.2.dll\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n./GameData/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Attachment System (mod)\u0022\u003EKAS\u003C/abbr\u003E/Plugins/KSPDev_Utils.1.2.dll\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n./GameData/KSPDev/LogConsole/Plugins/KSPDev_Utils.1.2.dll\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, I see in the KSPDev_Utils directory, there is also a 1.1 dll:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\n./GameData/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Inventory System (mod)\u0022\u003EKIS\u003C/abbr\u003E/Plugins/KSPDev_Utils.1.1.dll\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"IgorZ","CreatedById":155445,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-04-28T03:47:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis library is\u00A0shipped with the mods that use it. It\u0027s ok to have multiple copies in the game. Only one of each version will be loaded in the runtime.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-04-28T21:44:46Z\u0022 title=\u002204/28/2019 09:44  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EApril 28, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by IgorZ\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dizor","CreatedById":161502,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-11T00:07:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/155445-igorz/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022155445\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/155445-igorz/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@IgorZ\u003C/a\u003E, it would be nice if you inject this new \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/139024-17x-easyboard-v17-board-key-works-as-a-toggle/\u0026amp;do=findComment\u0026amp;comment=3648742\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Efeature\u003C/a\u003E from my \u003Cstrong\u003EEasyBoard\u003C/strong\u003E mod into yours \u003Cstrong\u003EEasy Vessel Switch\u003C/strong\u003E. I did not know about your mod when implementing this feature (thanks to \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/162363-wyzard/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022162363\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/162363-wyzard/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Wyzard\u003C/a\u003E for pointing to EVS). I think that your EVS is the right place for this \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wyzard","CreatedById":162363,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-11T01:34:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u2026Specifically, the feature being:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223648742\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022139024\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565475074\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022161502\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Dizor\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Dizor said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSkipping debris and flags when you switching vessels with \u0022 [ \u0022 and \u0022 ] \u0022 keys.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"IgorZ","CreatedById":155445,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-11T21:16:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223648793\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141180\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221565482078\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022161502\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Dizor\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 hours ago, Dizor said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/155445-igorz/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022155445\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/155445-igorz/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@IgorZ\u003C/a\u003E, it would be nice if you inject this new \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/139024-17x-easyboard-v17-board-key-works-as-a-toggle/\u0026amp;do=findComment\u0026amp;comment=3648742\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Efeature\u003C/a\u003E from my \u003Cstrong\u003EEasyBoard\u003C/strong\u003E mod into yours \u003Cstrong\u003EEasy Vessel Switch\u003C/strong\u003E. I did not know about your mod when implementing this feature (thanks to \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/162363-wyzard/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022162363\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/162363-wyzard/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Wyzard\u003C/a\u003E for pointing to EVS). I think that your EVS is the right place for this \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello. This feature looks reasonable for EVS. Thanks for the suggestion! I\u0027ve created a feature request.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"IgorZ","CreatedById":155445,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-10-24T04:55:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Ch1 style=\u0022background-color:#faf9fa;border-color:#a49fad;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;color:#6e6779;font-size:2.8rem;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.curseforge.com/kerbal/ksp-mods/easy-vessel-switch-evs/files\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E2.0 (October 23rd, 2019)\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/h1\u003E\n\u003Cul style=\u0022background-color:#faf9fa;border-color:#a49fad;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;color:#6e6779;font-size:12px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003E\u003Cli style=\u0022border-color:#a49fad;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;font-size:1.2rem;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003E\n[Change] KSP 1.8 compatibility.\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cstrong style=\u0022border-color:#a49fad;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;font-size:inherit;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003EWARNING\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003EMod versions of\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ccode style=\u0022border-color:#a49fad;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;color:#000000;font-size:inherit;padding:0px 1rem;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003Ev2.0\u003C/code\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Eand higher are not compatible to KSP versions prior to\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ccode style=\u0022border-color:#a49fad;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;color:#000000;font-size:inherit;padding:0px 1rem;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003E1.8\u003C/code\u003E!\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022border-color:#a49fad;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;font-size:1.2rem;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003E\n[Change] Upgrade to\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ccode style=\u0022border-color:#a49fad;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;color:#000000;font-size:inherit;padding:0px 1rem;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003EC# .Net 4.5\u003C/code\u003E.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022border-color:#a49fad;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;font-size:1.2rem;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003E\n[Enhancement] Add Chinese Simplified localization.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022border-color:#a49fad;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;font-size:1.2rem;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;\u0022\u003E\n[Enhancement] Add French localization. And fixing some doc strings.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"IgorZ","CreatedById":155445,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-03T10:51:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Ch2 style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003E\n2.1 (March, 3rd, 2020)\n\u003C/h2\u003E\n\u003Cul style=\u0022color:#333333;font-size:15.1181px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\n[Change] Switch to C# compiler v6.0.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n[Change] Set maximum KSP version to\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ccode style=\u0022background-color:#f9f2f4;color:#c7254e;font-size:13.6063px;padding:2px 4px;\u0022\u003E1.99\u003C/code\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Edue to now Squad team increases the minor part on\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cem\u003Eany\u003C/em\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Erelease, except a bugfix one (and it\u0027s the right way to treat versions!).\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n[Enhancement] Fixing typos in the default localization strings descriptions.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nP.S. Not yet available on CurseForge. They are historically behind the KSP release schedule \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AlphaRP","CreatedById":200831,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-03T18:28:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExcellent, thanks for the update!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tokamak","CreatedById":115593,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-22T18:16:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs this still meant to be the thread for EVS, or is there a newer one that I\u0027m missing? It clearly hasn\u0027t been active in a while.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m having some trouble with EVS, and was hoping to perhaps get a little help.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tonka Crash","CreatedById":189552,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-22T22:42:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223807542\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141180\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221592849763\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022115593\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Tokamak\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Tokamak said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs this still meant to be the thread for EVS, or is there a newer one that I\u0027m missing? It clearly hasn\u0027t been active in a while.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m having some trouble with EVS, and was hoping to perhaps get a little help.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is still the current thread.\u00A0 It\u0027s been updated since 1.9.1 came out and no one\u0027s reported problems since the last update. I haven\u0027t noticed any problems and I use it frequently in 1.9.1.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tokamak","CreatedById":115593,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-23T02:59:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223807663\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141180\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221592865768\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022189552\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Tonka Crash\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Tonka Crash said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is still the current thread.\u00A0 It\u0027s been updated since 1.9.1 came out and no one\u0027s reported problems since the last update. I haven\u0027t noticed any problems and I use it frequently in 1.9.1.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOkee. I just wanted to make sure, since the forum was giving me that canned warning that the thread was old, and I probably didn\u0027t want to add to it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat said, my problem went away as mysteriously as it came, so there\u0027s nothing to ask for help for. XD\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf anyone is curious later, or it comes up again, the problem was just one of EVS functionality seeming to disappear and take a vacation. Holding alt no longer gave the mouseover text, and alt-clicking on a vessel no longer switched vessels. It survived for multiple restarts of KSP, and then abruptly started working again, in the middle of a game session. XD It if happens again I\u0027ll provide logs and stuff.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHandy little mod, though! My one glitch notwithstanding.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"IgorZ","CreatedById":155445,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-28T05:51:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223807775\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141180\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221592881198\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022115593\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Tokamak\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 6/22/2020 at 7:59 PM, Tokamak said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf anyone is curious later, or it comes up again, the problem was just one of EVS functionality seeming to disappear and take a vacation. Holding alt no longer gave the mouseover text, and alt-clicking on a vessel no longer switched vessels. It survived for multiple restarts of KSP, and then abruptly started working again, in the middle of a game session. XD It if happens again I\u0027ll provide logs and stuff.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere was a version where it go broken due to the Unity update. It was fixed then. If you install your mods via \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E, then probably it was just an update?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyway, this thread is not stale or dead. There are not just many things to discuss - EVA is a simple and straightforward mod.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klarch","CreatedById":161516,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-18T17:33:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello. Is there any way to remove, or make transparent,\u00A0the box that comes up with vessel details when holding the ALT key?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe reason\u00A0I ask is that when I fly with camera in double right mouse click mode, I guess the cursor is right on the vessel and when I press ALT\u002BW or S to change the trim of the aircraft this box comes up and I\u0027d rather not see it. I tried changing the settings.cfg values to 0,0,0,0 like I did when I got rid of the part highlighting, but it didn\u0027t work. Thanks for any help.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"IgorZ","CreatedById":155445,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-22T23:33:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223895537\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141180\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221608312808\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022161516\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022klarch\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 12/18/2020 at 9:33 AM, klarch said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello. Is there any way to remove, or make transparent,\u00A0the box that comes up with vessel details when holding the ALT key?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe reason\u00A0I ask is that when I fly with camera in double right mouse click mode, I guess the cursor is right on the vessel and when I press ALT\u002BW or S to change the trim of the aircraft this box comes up and I\u0027d rather not see it. I tried changing the settings.cfg values to 0,0,0,0 like I did when I got rid of the part highlighting, but it didn\u0027t work. Thanks for any help.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlas, the overlay cannot be removed. I\u0027ve added a \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/ihsoft/EasyVesselSwitch/issues/33\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Efeature request\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klarch","CreatedById":161516,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-24T01:25:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223897850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141180\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221608680029\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022155445\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022IgorZ\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 12/22/2020 at 6:33 PM, IgorZ said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlas, the overlay cannot be removed. I\u0027ve added a \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/ihsoft/EasyVesselSwitch/issues/33\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Efeature request\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOK thanks for the info. If it can\u0027t be made transparent or removed, is there a way to change where it is displayed on screen (maybe in one of the corners where it will be less noticeable)?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"IgorZ","CreatedById":155445,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-24T22:21:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223898459\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141180\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221608773119\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022161516\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022klarch\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 hours ago, klarch said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOK thanks for the info. If it can\u0027t be made transparent or removed, is there a way to change where it is displayed on screen (maybe in one of the corners where it will be less noticeable)?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlas, no. The overlay layout is not customizable at all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"darthgently","CreatedById":204885,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-01-19T17:16:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve reached the point where I\u0027m video recording kOS automated flights and the great \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/JonnyOThan/KOS-stockcamera#description\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EkOS stock-camera addon \u003C/a\u003E is allowing me to control the mapview and flightview camera position, target, distance etc.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe ability to read and change the\u00A0Easy Vessel Switch\u00A0\u0027F7\u0027 mode from kOS script would allow me to\u00A0do a smooth switch between map and flight views (smooth transition targeting ship then smooth zoom\u00A0to ship in map, then switch to zoomed out in flight view (without EVS changing my camera distance or position) followed by\u00A0zoom in to normal flight view distance).\u00A0 I\u0027m only posting to get feedback or maybe get some gears turning.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI could\u00A0put a sticky note on my screen to remind me to entirely disable EVS prior to recording video, or manually change its mode as required, or uninstall EVS, but I\u0027m hoping to make this a one-click operation while still enjoying the nice functionality of EVS.\u00A0 There are times I want EVS functionality while recording video and being able to script its mode would remove a lot of \u0022oops\u0022 in the process.\u00A0 Is this a bad idea?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"IgorZ","CreatedById":155445,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-01-20T01:14:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223911594\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141180\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221611076618\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022204885\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022darthgently\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, darthgently said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve reached the point where I\u0027m video recording kOS automated flights and the great \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/JonnyOThan/KOS-stockcamera#description\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EkOS stock-camera addon \u003C/a\u003E is allowing me to control the mapview and flightview camera position, target, distance etc.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe ability to read and change the\u00A0Easy Vessel Switch\u00A0\u0027F7\u0027 mode from kOS script would allow me to\u00A0do a smooth switch between map and flight views (smooth transition targeting ship then smooth zoom\u00A0to ship in map, then switch to zoomed out in flight view (without EVS changing my camera distance or position) followed by\u00A0zoom in to normal flight view distance).\u00A0 I\u0027m only posting to get feedback or maybe get some gears turning.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI could\u00A0put a sticky note on my screen to remind me to entirely disable EVS prior to recording video, or manually change its mode as required, or uninstall EVS, but I\u0027m hoping to make this a one-click operation while still enjoying the nice functionality of EVS.\u00A0 There are times I want EVS functionality while recording video and being able to script its mode would remove a lot of \u0022oops\u0022 in the process.\u00A0 Is this a bad idea?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry, I don\u0027t quite get the question. Are\u00A0you looking for an API to interact with EVS from a script? Or do you need a new key binding that would simply disable/enable\u00A0EVS instead of iterating thru the stabilization modes (as F7 does)?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"darthgently","CreatedById":204885,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-01-20T01:17:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe first; an API to be accessed from a kOS script.\u00A0 But maybe it isn\u0027t valuable enough to enough people to implement.\u00A0 \u00A0I would understand\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"IgorZ","CreatedById":155445,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-01-20T01:22:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223911818\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141180\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221611105474\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022204885\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022darthgently\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, darthgently said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe first; an API to be accessed from a kOS script.\u00A0 But maybe it isn\u0027t valuable enough to enough people to implement.\u00A0 \u00A0I would understand\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis can be done. I\u0027ve created \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/ihsoft/EasyVesselSwitch/issues/35\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ea feature request\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"darthgently","CreatedById":204885,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-01-20T01:27:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223911822\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141180\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221611105765\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022155445\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022IgorZ\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, IgorZ said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis can be done. I\u0027ve created \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/ihsoft/EasyVesselSwitch/issues/35\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ea feature request\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks, IgorZ, truly appreciated \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/kerbal-forum-uploads/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"IgorZ","CreatedById":155445,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-01-20T06:43:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Ch1 style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;border-bottom:1px solid;color:#24292e;font-size:2em;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.curseforge.com/kerbal/ksp-mods/easy-vessel-switch-evs/files/3174663\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E2.2 (January 19th, 2021)\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/h1\u003E\n\u003Cul style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#24292e;font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#e74c3c;\u0022\u003E\u003Cu\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E[Change] Switch to KSP 1.11. There is no backwards compatibility!\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n[Change] Drop the old\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ccode style=\u0022font-size:13.6px;padding:.2em .4em;\u0022\u003EMiniAVC\u003C/code\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Ein favor of\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ccode style=\u0022font-size:13.6px;padding:.2em .4em;\u0022\u003EMiniAVC-V2\u003C/code\u003E.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n[Enhancement] Some fixes in French localization.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n[Fix\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/ihsoft/EasyVesselSwitch/issues/33\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E#33\u003C/a\u003E] Allow to disable the vessel overlay.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n[Fix\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/ihsoft/EasyVesselSwitch/issues/34\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E#34\u003C/a\u003E] Conflict with stock building system.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n[Fix\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/ihsoft/EasyVesselSwitch/issues/35\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E#35\u003C/a\u003E] Expose stabilization mode in API.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/204885-darthgently/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022204885\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/204885-darthgently/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@darthgently\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/161516-klarch/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022161516\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/161516-klarch/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@klarch\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-02-12T21:48:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis mod looks extremely promising, Imma try it tomorrow. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-02-13T04:07:27Z\u0022 title=\u002202/13/2021 04:07  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 13, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by SpaceX_Boi\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-20T01:25:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTried this mod, it is SO FREACKING GREAT!!!!!1111!11!! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI love it so much, switching between vessels is actually easy and fun to do now!!\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:heart_eyes:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/heart_eyes.png\u0022 title=\u0022:heart_eyes:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThx so much for the mod, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/155445-igorz/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022155445\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/155445-igorz/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@IgorZ\u003C/a\u003E! \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}